page.title: 13GAELIC PLACE-NAMES
page.content:
{Gaelic Place-names} Many places have had{Gaelic}names but in many instances their meaning is lost, because few people who live here are native gaelic speakers. 7760671{Fiacail Achadh-an-Liana } The tooth of Auchlany 775670{ Auchlany } The field of the meadow 777668{Breac Ruidh' or Ruigh' } Speckled sheiling 777674{Allt nan Cuinneag} The burn of the milk-pail (at its confluence with the {Garry,}which is a corruption { }of {garbh }meaning rough
